# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __enter__, __exit__, __call__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# All eighteen values are false; no decimal class implements the context
# manager or callable protocols in its own __dict__.
# decimal.Decimal is a numeric type defining many arithmetic operators
# but not the context manager or callable protocol. Context is a
# precision/rounding configuration object; the exception subclasses are
# error types. None define __enter__, __exit__, or __call__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

